javadoc:
Manages external program name changes and conflicts between the latest versioned
 program and the modified program being checked into version control.

methods.name: <init>
methods.comment:
Manages code unit changes and conflicts between the latest versioned
 program and the modified program being checked into version control.

params.name: mergeManager
params.comment: the top level merge manager for merging a program version.

params.name: resultPgm
params.comment:
the program to be updated with the result of the merge.
 This is the program that will actually get checked in.

params.name: originalPgm
params.comment: the program that was checked out.

params.name: latestPgm
params.comment: the latest checked-in version of the program.

params.name: myPgm
params.comment: the program requesting to be checked in.

params.name: latestChanges
params.comment: the address set of changes between original and latest versioned program.

params.name: myChanges
params.comment: the address set of changes between original and my modified program.

methods.javadoc:
For JUnit testing only, set the option for resolving a conflict.
@param decision CANCELED, ASK_USER, LATEST, MY, ORIGINAL
methods.name: setConflictDecision
methods.comment: For JUnit testing only, set the option for resolving a conflict.

params.name: decision
params.comment: CANCELED, ASK_USER, LATEST, MY, ORIGINAL

methods.javadoc: Clears all text from the information buffer.
methods.name: clearResolveInfo
methods.comment: Clears all text from the information buffer.

methods.javadoc:
This is a generic method for displaying the contents of the information
 buffer to the user.
methods.name: showResolveInfo
methods.comment:
This is a generic method for displaying the contents of the information
 buffer to the user.

methods.javadoc: Populate the reverse map for the Library symbols in the Original program.
methods.name: mapResultsToOriginalLibs
methods.comment: Populate the reverse map for the Library symbols in the Original program.

methods.javadoc: Populate the reverse map for the Library symbols in the Latest program.
methods.name: mapResultsToLatestLibs
methods.comment: Populate the reverse map for the Library symbols in the Latest program.

methods.javadoc: Populate the reverse map for the Library symbols in the My program.
methods.name: mapResultsToMyLibs
methods.comment: Populate the reverse map for the Library symbols in the My program.

methods.javadoc:
Gets symbol ID groups for each Library symbol that was in the Original program.
Note: This method excludes any new Library symbols in Original whose matching Result ID has already been placed in the resultIDsInAGroup set. Otherwise, each ID group that has a Result ID will add it to the resultIDsInAGroup set. @return the ID groups for Library symbols in the Original program.
methods.name: getGroupsForOriginalLibs
methods.comment:
Gets symbol ID groups for each Library symbol that was in the Original program.
  Note: This method excludes any new Library symbols in Original whose matching Result ID
 has already been placed in the resultIDsInAGroup set. Otherwise, each ID group that has a
 Result ID will add it to the resultIDsInAGroup set.

return.comment: the ID groups for Library symbols in the Original program.

methods.javadoc:
Gets symbol ID groups for each Library symbol that is new in the Latest program (symbol wasn't in the Original program).
Note: This method excludes any new Library symbols in Original whose matching Result ID has already been placed in the resultIDsInAGroup set. Otherwise, each ID group that has a Result ID will add it to the resultIDsInAGroup set. @return the ID groups for new Library symbols in the Latest program.
methods.name: getGroupsForLatestNewLibs
methods.comment:
Gets symbol ID groups for each Library symbol that is new in the Latest program
 (symbol wasn't in the Original program).
  Note: This method excludes any new Library symbols in Original whose matching Result ID
 has already been placed in the resultIDsInAGroup set. Otherwise, each ID group that has a
 Result ID will add it to the resultIDsInAGroup set.

return.comment: the ID groups for new Library symbols in the Latest program.

methods.javadoc:
Gets symbol ID groups for each Library symbol that is new in the My program (symbol wasn't in the Original program).
Note: This method excludes any new Library symbols in Original whose matching Result ID has already been placed in the resultIDsInAGroup set. Otherwise, each ID group that has a Result ID will add it to the resultIDsInAGroup set. @return the ID groups for new Library symbols in the My program.
methods.name: getGroupsForMyNewLibs
methods.comment:
Gets symbol ID groups for each Library symbol that is new in the My program
 (symbol wasn't in the Original program).
  Note: This method excludes any new Library symbols in Original whose matching Result ID
 has already been placed in the resultIDsInAGroup set. Otherwise, each ID group that has a
 Result ID will add it to the resultIDsInAGroup set.

return.comment: the ID groups for new Library symbols in the My program.

methods.name: removeExternalLibrary
methods.comment:
Removes the indicated external library from the indicated program version
 if it is empty.

params.name: program
params.comment: the program

params.name: libName
params.comment: the external library name

throws.comment: if there is no such enterrnal library in the program

methods.name: same
methods.comment: Determines whether the latest external program name and my external program name are equals.

params.name: latestName
params.comment: the latest external program name or null.

params.name: myName
params.comment: my external program name or null.

return.comment: true if the names are equal.

methods.name: mergeConflicts
methods.comment: Performs a manual merge of external program conflicts.

params.name: chosenConflictOption
params.comment:
ASK_USER means interactively resolve conflicts.
 JUnit testing also allows setting this to LATEST, MY, or ORIGINAL to force
 selection of a particular version change.

params.name: monitor
params.comment: task monitor for informing the user of progress.

throws.comment: if the user cancels the merge.

methods.name: showMergePanel
methods.comment: Displays the external program name conflict panel to the user.

params.name: idGroup
params.comment: the symbol ID group for the external program (Library) being merged.

params.name: monitor
params.comment: task monitor to provide merge status to the user and allow canceling.

methods.name: getConflictPanel
methods.comment: Gets the conflict resolution panel to display

params.name: idGroup
params.comment: the symbol ID group for the external program (Library) in conflict.

params.name: listener
params.comment: the listener for the user's choice when resolving the conflict.

methods.name: getExternalNameInfo
methods.comment: Returns an array of strings to display for a row of external program name information.

params.name: pgm
params.comment: the program version

params.name: extPgmName
params.comment: the external program name

params.name: prefix
params.comment: prefix for the first column's info.

params.name: suffix
params.comment: suffix for the first column's info.

return.comment: an array of strings (one for each column of the conflict choice table.

methods.name: getConflictInfo
methods.comment:
Gets the information to display at the top of the conflict window indicating
 which conflict this is of the total external program name conflicts.

params.name: idGroup
params.comment: the symbol ID group for the external program (Library) in conflict.

params.name: conflictIndex
params.comment: the index of the current conflict.

params.name: totalConflicts
params.comment: the total number of conflicts.

methods.name: merge
methods.comment:
Actually merges the indicated program name from the program version indicated
 by conflictOption into the result program.

params.name: idGroup
params.comment: the symbol ID group for the external program (Library) to merge.

params.name: chosenConflictOption
params.comment: conflict option indicating the program version the user chose.

params.name: monitor
params.comment: the task monitor for feedback and canceling.

methods.javadoc: Returns an array of symbol ID groups for all the external programs that are in conflict.
methods.name: getConflicts
methods.comment: Returns an array of symbol ID groups for all the external programs that are in conflict.

methods.name: mergeExternalProgramName
methods.comment:
Actually merges (sets or removes) the indicated external program name in
 program1 based on the same external program name in program2

params.name: program1
params.comment: the program to merge into.

params.name: program2
params.comment: the program to get the merge information from.

params.name: idGroup
params.comment: the symbol ID group for the external program (Library) to merge.

params.name: monitor
params.comment: task monitor for feedback or canceling the merge.s
